textBody:
CNO is a three-letter initialism. It can mean:

* Carrier-to-noise-density ratio, abbreviated C/N0 in the context of the GPS
* Casualty Notification Officer
* Chief Networking Officer
* Chief Nuclear Officer
* Chief Nursing Officer
* Chief of Naval Operations, typically the highest-ranking officer in the United States Navy 
* Chino Airport, IATA symbol: CNO
* Cis-Neptunian object
* CNO cycle, a special stellar nuclear fusion process
* Coconut Oil
* .com, .net, .org
* Computer network operations
* Conseco, under the New York Stock Exchange ticker symbol system

CNO may also refer to:

* The chemical formula for a fulminate ion
* Clozapine N-Oxide, used to activate synthetic biologiocal receptors in  DREADD technology
